<h3><strong>Create for mobile</strong></h3>
<p>While, most people intuitively use portrait or selfie mode when they record with their phones, that’s not the best practice for Instagram video. Most people view Instagram video on mobile, which means it’s best to <strong>shoot in vertical orientation</strong>.</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/instagram-video-3.png"><picture decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-322256">
<source type="image/webp" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/instagram-video-3.png.webp 439w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/instagram-video-3-310x509.png.webp 310w" sizes="(max-width: 439px) 100vw, 439px"/>
<img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/instagram-video-3.png" alt="phone screen showing typical example of vertical instagram video" width="439" height="721" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/instagram-video-3.png 439w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/instagram-video-3-310x509.png 310w" sizes="(max-width: 439px) 100vw, 439px"/>
</picture>
</a></p>
<p><em>Source: <a href="https://business.instagram.com/blog/announcing-instagram-reels">Instagram</a></em></p>
<p>Of course, there are some exceptions. For <strong>longer video content</strong>, horizontal video may be a better fit. Viewers can <strong>tilt their phone sideways</strong> for a full-screen viewing experience. Landscape video can also be uploaded to Stories and in-feed, but without the tilt effect.</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/instagram-video-4.png"><picture decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-322264">
<source type="image/webp" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/instagram-video-4-620x509.png.webp 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/instagram-video-4-310x255.png.webp 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/instagram-video-4-768x631.png.webp 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/instagram-video-4.png.webp 1230w" sizes="(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px"/>
<img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/instagram-video-4-620x509.png" alt="two phone screens showing how to view a horizontal instagram video" width="620" height="509" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/instagram-video-4-620x509.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/instagram-video-4-310x255.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/instagram-video-4-768x631.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/instagram-video-4.png 1230w" sizes="(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px"/>
</picture>
</a></p>
<p><em>Source: <a href="https://about.instagram.com/blog/announcements/igtv-now-supports-landscape-videos">Instagram</a></em></p>
<h3><strong>Provide value</strong></h3>
<p>To keep a viewer’s attention you need to <strong>make it worth their while.</strong> Try entertaining your audience through comic relief, captivating conversation, or your magnetic personality. Or, you could impart tips and tricks, how-to’s and workshops, or thought-provoking information.</p>
<p>In each Instagram video, <strong>your value proposition should be clear and simple</strong>. Before setting out to create a video, fill in the blank: When someone watches this video, they will _______. The answer may range from “laugh out loud” to “want to make breakfast cereal ice cream sandwiches” Whatever you land on, it should be clear to viewers upfront.</p>
<p>If you <strong>deliver on your promise</strong>, you’ll likely see more views, engagement, and shares. </p>
